        "text": "*Unternehmen Entebbe* namely reminded of the core of the German crimes, which are only imprecisely described in the name 'Auschwitz'. This core is formed by anti-Semitism and the memory that it was primarily Jews whom the Germans had destined for the gas chambers. But this disturbing realization had long since been pacified, especially by left-wing radical and left-liberal Germans. Some did so by making 'Auschwitz' an indescribable and thus historically singular (and consequently unrepeatable) place that could thereby be split off and whose victims (and surviving witnesses) could be silenced by paternalistically pathologizing them or classifying (and pushing away) their memories as subjectively colored. The others universalized the catastrophe in a leveling mixture of fascism theory and anti-imperialist phrases that ultimately had only one goal: to put themselves in the place of the victims."
