        "text": "Luhmann laid the theoretical foundation for his political sociology in 1968, with the essay *Soziologie des politischen Systems* (Sociology of the Political System). In it, he deals primarily with the differentiation of politics as an autonomous system of modern society. Luhmann still attributes the process of differentiation itself to role differentiation. In substance, however, his main focus is on the analysis of purely factual criteria of suitability and performance, which can only be negotiated immanently to the system, and which are used to fill and evaluate political roles (Luhmann 1968)."
