        "text": "(The Politics of Society) now represents the sum of all that Luhmann has contributed to the sociology of the political system in over 30 years. Specifically, the book comprises eleven chapters: 1. the politics of society, 2. the medium of power, 3. the differentiation and operational closure of the political system, 4. political decision-making, 5. the memory of politics, 6. the state of the political system, 7. political organizations, 8. public opinion, 9. self-descriptions, 10. structural couplings, 11. political evolution. Given the scarcity of space, not all aspects can be addressed. The central issues are power and violence, function and decision of the political system, and the political coding 'government' and 'opposition'."
